# Command Center environment

# Root of this repo. tasks/, signals/, drafts/, vault/, logs/ resolve under here.
COMMAND_CENTER_ROOT=/home/adrian/Developer/projects/command-center

# Vault (MACHINE-framework atomic-note KB). Phase 3 lights this up; phase 1+2 read legacy too.
VAULT_ROOT=/home/adrian/Developer/projects/command-center/vault

# Legacy sessions corpus (marketing-pipeline's KB). Read-only fallback.
LEGACY_SESSIONS_ROOT=/home/adrian/Documents/rolenext/sessions

# Dashboard port. 3001 during marketing-pipeline coexistence.
PORT=3001

# Processor per-tick cap. Maximum pending tasks dispatched per /api/cron tick
# for pipelines that don't declare their own `perTickCap` override. Default 3 —
# tuned to keep one tick under ~15 min worst case so 5-min cron firings don't
# overlap. Cheap pipelines (housekeeping, competitors) override this in their
# pipeline.config.ts.
PROCESSOR_PER_TICK_CAP=3

# Reddit-PMF (phase 5). Public JSON works without OAuth; UA is the only hard requirement.
REDDIT_USER_AGENT=command-center-reddit-pmf/0.1 (by /u/your-handle)
# Optional OAuth — uncomment + fill if you hit rate limits:
# REDDIT_CLIENT_ID=
# REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Vercel deploy (optional). If unset, deploy phase runs dry-run and only writes
# content files locally to signals/reddit-pmf/<date>/<cluster>/.
# VERCEL_TOKEN=
# VERCEL_PROJECT_ID=
# LANDING_REPO_PATH=/path/to/separate/landing-template-repo

# RoleNext job-apply pipeline. JWT is a Clerk session token — extract via
# `await window.Clerk.session.getToken()` in DevTools after logging into
# rolenext. Default-template tokens last ~60s; create a long-TTL JWT template
# in the Clerk dashboard for hour-long sessions.
ROLENEXT_API_BASE=http://localhost:8080
# ROLENEXT_JWT=
